    • compareTo

      public int compareTo​(Space anotherSpace)
      Compares this space level to the specified space level. The result is the value 0 if the space argument level is equal to this level; a value less than 0 if this level is less than the level argument; and a value greater than 0 if this level is greater than the level of the space argument. The values returned are the difference between the levels considered.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Space>
      Parameters:
      anotherSpace - The space to compare this space level against.
      Returns:
      the value 0 if the space argument level is equal to this level; a value less than 0 if this level is less than the level argument; and a value greater than 0 if this level is greater than the level of the space argument.
